Methods of Document Objects:
-->used to interact with and manipulate the document.
Getting Element:
1)Getting Element by Id : id=a single element, returns the element with the specified id.
2)Getting Element by Class : class = group ; 
3)Getting Element by Tag : 
4)Getting Element by using queryselector method: 

getElementByClassName();
-->returns all the elements having the same class name
-->returns an html collection object ;An html collection is a collection of nodes that can be accessed by index or by name.
-->It is an array of html elements.

Getting elements by Tagname:
getElementByTagName():
-->This method takes a tag name as string and returns an HTML collection object
-->each element loop

Getting Element by using queryselector method: 
-->The document query selector method select an HTML elements by tagname, by id, class name.
-->queryselector():can be used to select HTML element by its tagname, by id, class name; first matching element is returned.

-queryselectorAll():
-->it selects all the html elements by its class name and tagname.

>Manipulating Elements:
->To create HTML Elements:
createElement() - create a new element
    method - document.createElement()

